President Barack Obama and First Lady Michelle Obama released a statement on October 15, 2013, extending their best wishes to Muslims around the world on the occasion of Eid al-Adha. They also congratulated those performing the Hajj pilgrimage. The statement emphasized the shared roots of the world's Abrahamic faiths and highlighted the positive role that faith can play in motivating communities to address shared challenges. The Obamas expressed their warmest greetings and wished Eid Mubarak and Hajj Mabrour to all.